text:
Meeting with MOH

Decisions from MOH
1. Tech lead on the Ground - Agelgel - with the support of ALL they will be the SPOC for MOH
2. All the Content we produce will Need approval form MOH
3. Any support offers from anywhere to MOH will be channeled thru the SLACK

NAMING
We agreed that Common Name for all BOTS, Website,… will be: <http://COVID19.ET|COVID19.ET>

Below are the Categories we have formed we have put names against Tasks so Everyone that wants to help/or suggest improvements in these areas should address their conversation to the names against each task

I. AWARENESS

    1. IVR: Numbers are - 8335, 952
        1. Content - underway - @Samson
    2. CRBT
        1. EthioT to reconfigure to force people to hear the full message  - message should be short and punchy; suggestion is also to have various message and not always the same
    3. Instant Messaging -  @Samson
        1. SMS - To go live TODAY
        2. Telegram - underway - to go live SATURDAY
        3. WhatsApp - To go live SATURDAY
    4. Social Media Marketing -@Mike
        1. Facebook - the East African Office is engaged on fake news, Ads, Marketing and Verification
        2. Google
        3. Twitter

II. SURVEILLANCE & RESPONSE TEAM

This track to be Led by @Samson and @Yohanes all to Support them in achieving it

	2.1 SURVEILLANCE:

    1. At Port of Entry and for Door-to-Door Reporting
        1. Get all the official port of entries and Create an online Form <@UV8B0679P>
            1. Obtain sample form from MOH @Samson
    2. Public Reporting
        1. Configure it on the IVR to direct it to the Call Center
        2. Avail an App to the public for self reporting and 3rd part reporting
    3. Medical Centers Reporting
        1. Configure it on the IVR to always reach a medical professional

	2.2 RESPONSE

	1. Follow-up
		Avail a follow up platform and Connect it with all port of entries
	
	2. Suspicious Cases Analysis from the Call Center
		Ensure we have Alerts from the call centre reporting

    3. Rapid Response - getting alerts from the Case Analysts above
	
III. ISOLATION
This track to be led by <@UV8B0679P> / <@UV81AMFSP> all others to support
    1. Follow up systems  integrated with the Response follow up system
        1. Call
        2. SMS
        3. App or Bot

IV INFORMATION SHARING FOR HELATH PROFESSIONALS
crowd source ideas for this on how tech can play a role

V CROSS CUTTING

1. Data center environment, servers, redundancies/ fail overs - @Samson to connect with Meried (IE NETWORKS)
2. Data repository for Analysis/ AI,… TBD - Ideas welcome

text: <@UV8B0679P> The sources we would have right now are through commcare and the bots. I don’t see why we shouldn’t be able to send it all to one Database and query from there. Thank you for joining us <@U010318AHEE>... I just discovered Hakim yesterday and was hoping to get a POC. This is perfect timing.

We are gathering 2 things regarding how to assist the healthcare folks in Ethiopia and saving it in a google drive.

1. What information can we share with the healthcare workers so they can protect themselves? This is urgent so we need this in a PDF version first. And we need it to be translated in the main languages. 
2. How can we aid in providing protective gear? DIY masks etc... 

The goal is to drive these two initiatives to completion within the next 24-48 hours...We will need your help with these initiatives.

elements.text: Thank you for joining us

... I just discovered Hakim yesterday and was hoping to get a POC. This is perfect timing.

We are gathering 2 things regarding how to assist the healthcare folks in Ethiopia and saving it in a google drive.
What information can we share with the healthcare workers so they can protect themselves? This is urgent so we need this in a PDF version first. And we need it to be translated in the main languages.
How can we aid in providing protective gear? DIY masks etc...
The goal is to drive these two initiatives to completion within the next 24-48 hours...We will need your help with these initiatives.

text:
Thank you Keneni for helping in this fight.

1. There is a facebook group for health professionals in Ethiopia who have been sharing documents, so we could gather some from there. Also WHO has a lot of resources. 
Regarding translation, the language of instruction and work is English so I dont see the need to translate unless it is for the consumption of the public. However, it may be best to simplify the content to be used as a quick reference

2. Providing protective gear is very important, especially for interns who are the front line health workers in most government hospitals in Addis. They are not being provided with all they need. Their lack of experience may put them at a higher risk. They will benefit from sanitizers, and N95 masks.
